cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

The paper deals with the problem of radio fingerprinting, which is a subfield of wireless security. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a system that optimizes deep learning-based radio fingerprinting algorithms without retraining the underlying deep learning model. This involves mapping inputs onto a very large feature space, which is a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also deals with wireless communication and networking, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes a system that can counteract the action of the wireless channel, which is a control engineering problem. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with information theory, as it investigates whether an adversary can successfully impersonate another device fingerprint. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible category.
